Spencer Fons is wondering if an email account can be made for the Greek Council. This would behave similar to how some departments have their own department email account that can be linked to other user's accounts. Is this something we can do?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dana,
We mostly want it so we can have an email to handoff to the Executive Board for following years instead of having to start new with the President’s or Secretary’s email every year.
We will mostly use the email account to send out emails to all Greeks and also create a shared calendar from an official, central account.
We would really like to have a shared calendar for all Greeks to be able to view. Although if I share it from my personal account this year, next year’s president would have to create a whole new shared calendar. For comparison, I would like to be able to have it similar to how Student Life has set up their new Events Calendar for the entire school, although this calendar will be focused mainly on the Greek Community.
Just to be clear, we are not sharing the email password account with all Greeks. Only a few positions in the organization would have access to the account information.
Let me know if you have any questions.
Thank you,
Spencer Fons Greek Council – President Architectural Engineering 2017 Milwaukee School of Engineering
helpdesk-note.body-html:

We mostly want it so we can have an email to handoff to the Executive Board for following years instead of having to start new with the President’s or Secretary’s email every year.

We would really like to have a shared calendar for all Greeks to be able to view. Although if I share it from my personal account this year, next year’s president would have to create a whole new shared calendar.
For comparison, I would like to be able to have it similar to how Student Life has set up their new Events Calendar for the entire school, although this calendar will be focused mainly on the Greek Community.
 
Just to be clear, we are not sharing the email password account with all Greeks. Only a few positions in the organization would have access to the account information.
 
Let me know if you have any questions.
 
Thank you,
 
Spencer Fons
Greek Council – President
Architectural Engineering 2017
Milwaukee School of Engineering

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Spencer,
Thank you for sharing the additional information as to how you would leverage the email account. I looked into what SUB has done as an example and they are running an msoe-sub@gmail.com account. Their intent is to be able to share it for years to come and not worry about the access you are encountering right now. Is that something that might work for you?

Please let me know what you decide. What I am able to provide would not create an email account so we will need to revisit this with IT if needed.
Sincerely, Dana Grennier Digital Marketing Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2721

Hi Dana,

Thank you,

On Wed, 11 Nov at 11:46 am , fonss <fonss@msoe.edu> wrote:
Hi Dana,
 
We mostly want it so we can have an email to handoff to the Executive Board for following years instead of having to start new with the President’s or Secretary’s email every year.
 
We will mostly use the email account to send out emails to all Greeks and also create a shared calendar from an official, central account.
 
We would really like to have a shared calendar for all Greeks to be able to view. Although if I share it from my personal account this year, next year’s president would have to create a whole new shared calendar.
For comparison, I would like to be able to have it similar to how Student Life has set up their new Events Calendar for the entire school, although this calendar will be focused mainly on the Greek Community.
 
Just to be clear, we are not sharing the email password account with all Greeks. Only a few positions in the organization would have access to the account information.
 
Let me know if you have any questions.
 
Thank you,
 
Spencer Fons
Greek Council – President
Architectural Engineering 2017
Milwaukee School of Engineering

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Hans,
When we reimage your computer all of your files and programs will be deleted from the hard drive. Any files that you wish to keep must be backed-up elsewhere. There are many options that you can use to back up your files. MSOE provides Box accounts for all Students/Staff/Faculty to use. If you go to box.msoe.edu and log in with your MSOE credentials, you will be able to upload your files into the Box servers. If you need instructions for that, click here. You mention that you have been backing up your files onto an external drive. This is great! Any measures that you take to keep your files safe from hard drive failures makes us happy. We still recommend backing up to Box or Google Drive to be extra safe, but generally backing up on an external drive is good enough.
If you would like us to install programs for you when you come in to get the reimage, please let the person that you talk to know what you need. We are happy to get everything set up for you.
I am going to close this ticket until we see you at the desk. Please feel free to reply or contact us again with any more inquiries.
Have a great day!

Have a great day!

helpdesk-note.body:
Dear Andy, Thank you for looking into this matter. I cannot tell from the response if the matter is fixed. I worked personally with Pat Hurlburt and she could not fix this. It does not matter what computer we use and students who are IT specialists could not get this to work. Could the company fix this? I need to have audio to do my job, I am not the only professor that has this issue. I had guest speakers from the military, VA and Aurora. All were amazed that at MSOE, we do not have working technology.
I do not know who else to contact but if there is no working equipment in the classrooms I will not be able to do my job. I lost a whole semester waiting for this to be fixed. Can you please get back to me with a definite answer. I am so happy this may be fixed. Please help.
Catherine Leffler MSN RN Assistant Professor of Nursing
Milwaukee School of Engineering - SON 1025 N. Broadway, Milwaukee, WI 262-822-2230 Cellphone (text preffered) Are you a nurse interested in becoming an influential nurse leader and manager? Visit www.msoe.edu/msn<http://www.msoe.edu/msn> to learn about our MSN Health Care Systems Management program. “

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Krueger Hall card reader lab 201
helpdesk-ticket.description: The door to our KH lab doesn’t lock anymore. People can just walk right in, and they are. I think it’s the lock itself, not the card reader. Can you send someone to take a look. -Jordan Weston Facilities Maintenance looked into the issue, once you swipe your ID card to unlock the door it unlocks, but will not re-lock unless you use your key. Possibly something with the card reader???
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
The door to our KH lab doesn’t lock anymore. People can just walk right in, and they are. I think it’s the lock itself, not the card reader. Can you send someone to take a look.
-Jordan Weston

Facilities Maintenance looked into the issue, once you swipe your ID card to unlock the door it unlocks, but will not re-lock unless you use your key. Possibly something with the card reader???

helpdesk-note.body: Sent to Hardware Team.
helpdesk-note.body-html: Sent to Hardware Team.

helpdesk-note.body: I am going to run over and take a look real quick.
helpdesk-note.body-html: I am going to run over and take a look real quick.

helpdesk-note.body: The physical lock on the door seems to be faulty. The door should re-lock when someone uses their ID to get in, and it does work correctly some times. More often then not it doesn't work. When malfunctioning, and when turning the handle on the door to get in you can feel it trying to resist and stay locked but with a little bit more force the handle turns and you can open the door. Myself and the workers in the RPC in KH believe that it is a mechanical issue with the lock and not the functionality of the card swipe reader. I am going to create a maintenance ticket for this issue and leave this one open for a few days just in case.

Regards,
Chaning Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2775 why is the helpdesk ticket request in "my news" on the school website. This was extremely un-intuitive and I was only able to find it because someone I know had found it previously. This caused a lot of frustration and time lost. It would also be nice to know requests for AV equipment are now through the helpdesk ticket system. It took two bounced emails to even know were to look. Again, very frustrating and lots of time lost. A PSA would be nice. Student Life has the emails of all the student leaders and this is information we should not have to dig and search and re-search to find.

helpdesk-note.body: Chaning, AV service requests should be done through Ad Astra as they always have been done, not the helpdesk. AV helpdesk tickets should be reqeusts for things like burned out bulbs, not events. We need to coordinate with the room reservations, and we do not want to be responsible for the AV if a room request was denied. We did do training with Student Life and all the organization leaders, and they are aware of the Ad Astra process. Pat

Pat

helpdesk-note.body: I spoke with Michael Timm about this to see if he can see anything behind the scenes. The only things blocked from attachments are .bat and .exe files. If we do strip an attachment, an email is sent back to the sender stating stating an attachment has been blocked. Nothing looks like we blocked an attachment. helpdesk-ticket.subject: WMSE Studio Computers
helpdesk-ticket.description: Good day. I am Matt Rockwell, the designated Chief Engineer at WMSE radio. I am seeking to install broadcast software on the windows computers in the WMSE studios and am looking for the best way to do this. What I seek is Administrator access to WMSE computers which are on the MSOE domain. As a contractor, I do not currently have a MSOE netid. Would it be best for me to have an account with designated Administrator rights, create a generic "Technical Director" account with Administrator rights, or create a local account on each machine? Is there a possible alternate solution? I am certainly open to any suggestion which works best for MSOE IT. The machines on the domain with which I am currently working with are as follows: A-Studio StudioA StudioB If needed, any information can be verified with Thomas Crawford, the WMSE General Manager. I am currently at x7557, or I can be reached via my cell @ 608-345-1972. Thank you very much for your time and support! Kindest regards, Matt Rockwell
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Good day. I am Matt Rockwell, the designated Chief Engineer at WMSE radio.  I am seeking to install broadcast software on the windows computers in the WMSE studios and am looking for the best way to do this.

What I seek is Administrator access to WMSE computers which are on the MSOE domain. As a contractor, I do not currently have a MSOE netid.  Would it be best for me to have an account with designated Administrator rights, create a generic "Technical Director" account with Administrator rights, or create a local account on each machine? Is there a possible alternate solution?  I am certainly open to any suggestion which works best for MSOE IT.

The machines on the domain with which I am currently working with are as follows:
  • A-Studio
  • StudioA
  • StudioB
If needed, any information can be verified with Thomas Crawford, the WMSE General Manager.

I am currently at x7557, or I can be reached via my cell @ 608-345-1972.

Thank you very much for your time and support!

Kindest regards,
Matt Rockwell

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Matt Rockwell, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2812
We are unable to give you domain access, however, they should be able to give you a local account on the machines. I will be marking this as resolved, however, if you have any additional questions or concerns please do not hesitate to contact us.
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.description:
I don't see a search box anywhere on the MSOE web site. For example, I was looking for the final exam schedule. I couldn't search that phrase nor could I search for the Registrar's office. I found it under student resources under my news, but aren't things supposed to be easier to find on the web?
Mitch Colton
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I don’t see a search box anywhere on the MSOE web site.  For example, I was looking for the final exam schedule.  I couldn’t search that phrase nor could I search for the Registrar’s office.  I found it under student resources under my news, but aren’t things supposed to be easier to find on the web?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mitch Colton,
We are currently working on making the website's search engine more effective. The search box is located on the upper right corner of the homepage, at times it takes a second to load.
What I would suggest is using Google to find MSOE information. I personally do not use the search engine that MSOE provides, Google often provides sufficient results.
If you have any other issues, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Thank you for your time. Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2814

helpdesk-ticket.subject: connection error on Copy Machine CC 2nd floor
helpdesk-ticket.description: The copy machine on the second floor of the CC is not letting anyone log in and presents a "Connection Error" instead. This occurred for 3 different users. A quick look on network port lights showed that the copy machine has a connection to the network. Thanks
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
The copy machine on the second floor of the CC is not letting anyone log in and presents a "Connection Error" instead. This occurred for 3 different users. A quick look on network port lights showed that the copy machine has a connection to the network.
Thanks

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jacob Ertel, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2841 The copy machine on the second floor of the CC is not letting anyone log in and presents a "Connection Error" instead. This occurred for 3 different users. A quick look on network port lights showed that the copy machine has a connection to the network. Thanks
Thank you for taking the time to submit this incident. I stopped down by the CC 2nd floor Konica Minolta and there was a crowd of people using the machine to print finals study notes. I observed 4 people successfully log in and print output. I successfully logged in as myself and printed my test page as well. I looked for printer logs on the server to see if I could identify the error but I could not. I can only suspect this was a temporary issue. I am marking this incident as resolved. Please contact the Help Desk with any additional questions or concerns. Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Jacob Ertel,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2841
The copy machine on the second floor of the CC is not letting anyone log in and presents a "Connection Error" instead. This occurred for 3 different users. A quick look on network port lights showed that the copy machine has a connection to the network.
Thanks

Thank you for taking the time to submit this incident.  I stopped down by the CC 2nd floor Konica Minolta and there was a crowd of people using the machine to print finals study notes.  I observed 4 people successfully log in and print output.  I successfully logged in as myself and printed my test page as well.  I looked for printer logs on the server to see if I could identify the error but I could not.  I can only suspect this was a temporary issue.  I am marking this incident as resolved.  Please contact the Help Desk with any additional questions or concerns.

Peter Pfister
Help Desk Coordinator
414.277.7202

Good luck - and thanks for your efforts.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: InfoMaker Executable problem, nested report
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Please forward to tier 3 for InfoMaker. I have 2 reports that I built. I'd like to add one to the other as nested report; I'm missing something in the process. I tried to build a executable with the two reports and get a error: "CO193: One or more of the files in your library list could not be opened for write." It's been awhile since I've done an executable and can't remember what this error means.
Thanks. Sheila
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Please forward to tier 3 for InfoMaker.  I have 2 reports that I built.  I’d like to add one to the other as nested report; I’m missing something in the process.  I tried to build a executable with the two reports and get a error:  “CO193: One or more of the files in your library list could not be opened for write.”  It’s been awhile since I’ve done an executable and can’t remember what this error means.
 
Thanks.
Sheila

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Sheila To get rid of the error “CO193: One or more of the files in your library list could not be opened for write.”
Do the following:
In infomaker go to File, Library List. Highlight the text and copy it to notepad. Then delete it from the library list window. Then build the executable. You can't build the executable with those 2 libraries in there because they are read only and it throws that error. See attached screen shot of what to remove. After you are done building the executable then go back and paste those libraries back in the Library List (File->Library List) and and say apply & ok. Another way to put those libraries back is to run the InfoMaker Configuration Tool.
Thanks Beth Tyriver

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Laptop Program General Question
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
To my understanding the laptop program has a two year cycle where a new laptop is distributed to the students every two years. I was wondering if you could keep the same laptop for 3 years and then maybe not have to pay the technology fee? Also if this is possible and the student gets a new laptop for their fourth year and graduate, do they get to keep that laptop if all the software is taken off of it.
Thank you for your time,
Adam Wright Milwaukee School of Engineering 2018 Biomedical Engineering wrightam@msoe.edu
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,
 
To my understanding the laptop program has a two year cycle where a new laptop is distributed to the students every two years. I was wondering if you could keep the same laptop for 3 years and then maybe not have to pay the technology fee? Also if this is possible and the student gets a new laptop for their fourth year and graduate, do they get to keep that laptop if all the software is taken off of it.
 
Thank you for your time,
 
Adam Wright
Milwaukee School of Engineering 2018
Biomedical Engineering
wrightam@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Adam,
You are correct that you will receive a new laptop after two years at MSOE. You are charged for the technology fee based on your status as an undergraduate, so even if the option is available to keep the laptop you will still be charged the technology fee throughout your undergraduate years. At this time there is no option to keep the laptop for a third year. It must be returned when that time comes.
Thank you, Shawna Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2913

Hi Paula Harrold, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2918 Need info on how to start a Nursing Box.com account. Please see Attachment. INFO from EECS Chair. Who would be the "owner" of the Box.com for Nursing? How is it set up?
Ticket attachments : 1. BOX_QUESTION_FOR_NURSING.docx
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Paula Harrold,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2918
Need info on how to start a Nursing Box.com account. Please see Attachment. INFO from EECS Chair.
Who would be the "owner" of the Box.com for Nursing? How is it set up?
Ticket attachments : 1. BOX_QUESTION_FOR_NURSING.docx

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Paula Harrold,
Please ignore that last email - I sent before I'd added content.
Two things:
One, Box and our Single Sign On process are not designed to be used the way the EECS and RSOB accounts are using it. They have legacy generic accounts that were created in the system long before Box and single sign-on were introduced. Accounts are created vastly differently now by an automated system that links all of our domains together and provide access to (currently) ten different websites and systems. Each account is assigned to a user, and no generic accounts can be created any longer. EECS and RSOB are grandfathered to a Box account based on a system we have replaced.
Box is also not intended for generic folders, the product is not designed the same way as we think about Windows and Active Directory accounts. Box intends for a user to own a folder or document, and to share it with collaborators. So rather than log into Box as "Nursing@msoe.edu", you would log in with your own account (you are automatically logged in with this account be default, as Box is one of our Single-Sign on partners) and you will have access to a shared folder you would call School of Nursing Faculty and School of Nursing Chair and Program Directors. You would then share those folders with anyone who wants access, you have full control over what files they can access, and if they have read/write/delete permissions.
Below is the material that we send to end users just getting started with Box
----------------
A box.com folder can be shared with anyone you'd like. It can be shared to individual users, or it can be shared with anyone that has the link, it can be passworded, or made public. However, box.com is not related to MSOE MS Active Directory - meaning there are only folders and accounts for individual users. There are not folders for departments, or groups like in email. The two systems are separate companies (Microsoft and Box) and at this time, there is not a method to combine the folder or group hierarchy. Below are two links for setting up and using Box. One is a doc created by Mike Timm here at MSOE that is customized to the MSOE environment. The other link comes directly from Box and explains detailed use of their product. http://www.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-3261 http://boxuniversity.litmos.com/online-courses FOLDERS CANNOT BE CREATED WITH ACTIVE DIRECTORY GROUP ACCESS. Box and Microsoft Active Directory unfortunately are not linked at this time; the companies do not share a method to incorporate group access. Thanks,
Paul Fabian Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2918 Need info on how to start a Nursing Box.com account. Please see Attachment. INFO from EECS Chair. Who would be the "owner" of the Box.com for Nursing? How is it set up?
Ticket attachments : 1. BOX_QUESTION_FOR_NURSING.docx
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Paula Harrold,

Please ignore that last email - I sent before I'd added content.

Two things: 

One, Box and our Single Sign On process are not designed to be used the way the EECS and RSOB accounts are using it. They have legacy generic accounts that were created in the system long before Box and single sign-on were introduced. Accounts are created vastly differently now by an automated system that links all of our domains together and provide access to (currently) ten different websites and systems. Each account is assigned to a user, and no generic accounts can be created any longer. EECS and RSOB are grandfathered to a Box account based on a system we have replaced.

Box is also not intended for generic folders, the product is not designed the same way as we think about Windows and Active Directory accounts. Box intends for a user to own a folder or document, and to share it with collaborators. So rather than log into Box as "Nursing@msoe.edu", you would log in with your own account (you are automatically logged in with this account be default, as Box is one of our Single-Sign on partners) and you will have access to a shared folder you would call School of Nursing Faculty and School of Nursing Chair and Program Directors. You would then share those folders with anyone who wants access, you have full control over what files they can access, and if they have read/write/delete permissions. 

Below is the material that we send to end users just getting started with Box

----------------

A box.com folder can be shared with anyone you'd like. It can be shared to individual users, or it can be shared with anyone that has the link, it can be passworded, or made public. However, box.com is not related to MSOE MS Active Directory - meaning there are only folders and accounts for individual users. There are not folders for departments, or groups like in email. The two systems are separate companies (Microsoft and Box) and at this time, there is not a method to combine the folder or group hierarchy.
Below are two links for setting up and using Box. One is a doc created by Mike Timm here at MSOE that is customized to the MSOE environment. The other link comes directly from Box and explains detailed use of their product. 
http://www.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-3261
http://boxuniversity.litmos.com/online-courses
FOLDERS CANNOT BE CREATED WITH ACTIVE DIRECTORY GROUP ACCESS. Box and Microsoft Active Directory unfortunately are not linked at this time; the companies do not share a method to incorporate group access.
Thanks,

Paul Fabian

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Dave,
Java recently put out an update that ADP requires in order to work properly. In order to install the new update, go to this link. https://www.java.com/en/download/
Once you have installed it and open ADP up again, make sure that you allow java to run on the ADP webpage in case it prompts you with a security question. If it still doesn't work after all of this I would recommend installing the newest version of Mozilla Firefox here. https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new/
If you run into any issues trying to install the two items please let me know, I would be glad to help out.
Best Regards, Sam West MSOE IT - Assistant Systems Administrator

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Outlook Connection Issues
helpdesk-ticket.description: My Outlook application on my laptop is having connection issues. Near the bottom right corner it just says "Disconnected." All of my other internet services are working properly. I have recently changed my password, so I feel this may have something to do with that.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: My Outlook application on my laptop is having connection issues. Near the bottom right corner it just says "Disconnected." All of my other internet services are working properly. I have recently changed my password, so I feel this may have something to do with that.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mike Osep,
The issue that you are having with outlook is most likely due to a small bug within the application itself, that causes Outlook to not prompt the user to update the password. This can be fixed fairly easy with the following.
1. go to the start menu within windows 2. type credential manager into the search bar 3. Hit enter 4. A new window should open with various windows credentials 5. In the bottom "generic credentials" section there should be an MS.outlook15"youremail@.msoe.edu 6. click the down arrow on right side and remove it from vault 7. select yes if a prompt box appears 8. restart the outlook application and you should now be prompted to enter in new password 9. Emails should now start syncing.
Let us know if you have any issues. Have a nice day.

From: Helpdesk [mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu] Sent: Wednesday, November 18, 2015 12:09 To: All Faculty; All Staff; All Students Subject: Revised Update: Information Technology Outage Notice Importance: High
MSOE Community,
Through working with our vendor Dell, we have determined that there has been a hardware equipment failure in our DataCenter. Dell will be coming to replace this equipment this evening. As a result, there will be an electronic services outage this evening from 10:00 p.m. - 4:00 a.m.
Major services will be down including:
* community.msoe.edu (main website will still be up) * Blackboard (you can still access directly at msoe.blackboard.com) * Email access * Printing Services
*

* Campus Phone System * Public Safety Systems
Should you experience an emergency during this time and are unable to use the phone system, you can reach Public Safety at 414-291-5133.
Thank you for your continued patience as we resolve these issues.
No MSOE IT employees nor any MSOE IT correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
